## What is Global Pause?
A protocol-wide emergency stop that:
- Is controlled by admin (requires capability to toggle)
- Lives in a SHARED config/state object (affects all users)
- Is checked by multiple sensitive functions before operating
- Single source of truth (one field controls pause state)

NOT global pause:
- Per-object locks (offer.is_locked, position.frozen)
- User-controlled state flags
- Local reentrancy guards

